1951;;The Red Badge of Courage;;American;;John Huston;;Audie Murphy, Bill Mauldin;;war;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Red_Badge_of_Courage_(film);;The plot is based on the book with fewer bloody details. A regiment of Union soldiers head South to engage Confederate forces. Joining them is Henry Fleming (Audie Murphy), a green private sent into battle for the first time. He is unprepared for the fight, but by the time battle breaks out, he finds his endurance and courage tested.[3]